   430	
   431	GitHub Actions' `ubuntu-latest` runners ship with Docker and the
   432	Compose v2 plugin pre-installed; no extra setup needed.
   433	
   434	We do **not** add `compose-smoke` to branch protection in this PR.
   435	Reasoning: the existing required checks (`docs-lint`,
   436	`schema-validity`, `python-lint`, `python-typecheck`, `python-test`,
   437	`schema-parity`) are sufficient to gate a 10a merge; adding
   438	`compose-smoke` to protection on the *same* PR that introduces it
   439	risks a chicken-and-egg if the job is flaky on first run. Add to
   440	protection in 10b once the job has a few clean runs under its belt.
