   532	
   533	## Out of Scope
   534	
   535	- Any Dockerfile for an EDEN service (`task-store-server`,
   536	  `orchestrator`, etc.). 10b.
   537	- Any `PostgresStore` Python code. Lands when its consumer lands —
   538	  10b.
   539	- Any blob storage Python code. 10d.
   540	- The `setup-experiment` script. 10c.
   541	- Gitea admin user / API token bootstrap. 10c.
   542	- Production-grade secrets management. The `.env` pattern is
   543	  developer-grade; production deployments override.
   544	- Compose overrides for the e2e test. 10e may add a `compose.test.yaml`.
   545	- Branch protection update to require `compose-smoke`. Deferred to
   546	  a follow-up after the job is proven stable.
   547	
   548	## Known Risks / Things to Watch
   549	
   550	- **GitHub Actions Docker version drift.** `ubuntu-latest` updates
   551	  Docker periodically; Compose v2 syntax we use (`--wait`,
   552	  `--wait-timeout`, `name:` top-level field, no `version:` key) all
   553	  require Docker Compose v2.20+. As of April 2026 `ubuntu-latest`
   554	  ships v2.27+, so we have margin, but if the runner ever
   555	  downgrades the smoke job will break loudly. We don't pin Docker
   556	  in CI because GitHub controls that.
   557	- **Gitea startup is slow.** First boot of `gitea/gitea:1.22.6-rootless`
   558	  takes 15-25 seconds on a cold runner. The healthcheck
   559	  `start_period: 30s` covers this; if it ever proves flaky,
   560	  the next move is bumping to 60s rather than reducing the test.
   561	- **Image-pin staleness.** `postgres:16.6-alpine` and
   562	  `gitea/gitea:1.22.6-rootless` will be superseded. We pin
   563	  deliberately; Phase 10e or a dedicated bump PR refreshes both
   564	  together when the next Compose round lands.
   565	- **Port-collision regret.** Defaults of 5433 / 3001 / 2222 sidestep
   566	  the most common collisions but a developer running their own
   567	  Gitea on 3001 will hit one. The README's Troubleshooting section
   568	  documents the `.env` overrides; no other mitigation is worth it.
   569	- **`.env.example` rotation.** The dev-only secrets in `.env.example`
   570	  are intentionally weak. If a future contributor copies them to a
   571	  real deployment they're in trouble. The README's Quickstart
   572	  section labels the values as throwaway; we additionally make
   573	  `POSTGRES_PASSWORD`, `GITEA_SECRET_KEY`, `GITEA_INTERNAL_TOKEN`
   574	  required-with-error-on-missing in `compose.yaml`, so production
   575	  users who delete `.env` get a clear failure rather than silently
   576	  inheriting weak defaults.
   577	- **Compose project-name leakage.** The `name: eden-reference`
   578	  field means volumes get the prefix `eden-reference_`. If a
   579	  developer also runs the predecessor's direvo monolith via
   580	  Compose, project names won't collide. If they ever rename our
   581	  `name:` field, every `docker volume ls` reference and every
   582	  `compose down -v` invocation that targets historical data will
   583	  miss the old volumes. We document the project name in the README.
   584	- **Compose v1 (`docker-compose`) users.** v1 is EOL since June
   585	  2023. Some legacy systems still ship it; those users will see
   586	  syntax errors on `name:` and `--wait`. The README's prerequisites
   587	  section names `docker compose` v2.20+ explicitly. No backcompat
   588	  shim.
   589	
   590	## Files to Reference
   591	
   592	- `direvo/Dockerfile` — predecessor's container shape, kept for
   593	  10b context but **not** copied for 10a.
   594	- `docs/roadmap.md` — Phase 10 unit definitions.
   595	- `reference/README.md` — current "Compose: Phase 10" placeholder
   596	  that this chunk updates.
   597	- The Postgres image docs (`hub.docker.com/_/postgres`) for
   598	  `POSTGRES_*` env-var semantics and `/docker-entrypoint-initdb.d/`
   599	  rules.
   600	- The Gitea install docs
   601	  (`docs.gitea.com/installation/install-with-docker-rootless`) for
   602	  `GITEA__*` env-var semantics and rootless-image conventions.

